    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Very broad, flat adzes having a spur or punch on the back of the head which can be used as a nail set.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000005711/Blackburn, Illustrated Encyclopedia of Woodworking Handtools (1974)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeer brede, platte bijlen die een priem of een drevel aan de achterkant van de kop hebben die dienst kan doen om gaten voor spijkers te maken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052490/Clason, Elsevier tools and ironware (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>形狀非常寬闊且平坦的扁斧，斧背有一尖刺或鑽孔器，可作為壓釘桿使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
